  <body>
    <section name="Request Publication of Document">
      <span class="shortdesc">How to ask the editor to publish a document?</span>
   
   <script type="text/javascript">
    leftpx=300;
    heightpx=300;
   </script>
   <div class='group'>
    <div id='screenshot'><div>
      <img src="../../../../images/screenshots/cms_M9/contribs/goto_request_schedule_publication.png" alt='request schedule publication screenshot'/>
    </div></div>
    <p>
      Requesting publication of the document 'multibazaar2009'. 
      <a href='./request_publication.html'>A window will popup</a> where you can schedule at 
      what date and time you want the publication to occur.

      The editor will be notified and accept or reject this request.
    </p>
   </div>

   <p>
    In a document in <a href='../concepts/view_mode.html'>view mode</a>, e.g. after
    <a href='./save_document.html'>saving that document</a>, 
    click the 'schedule publication (request)' 
    button at the top to request that the document be published.
   </p>
   <p>
    The editor will be notified and accept or reject your request.
   </p>

